Inline styles
Internal CSS
External CSS

CSS syntax: one selectors and one/more declarations
CSS declarations: one property and one value
e.g.
h1
  {
  color:blue;
  text-align:center
  }

CSS comments: /* this is a comment */

Embedding an external stylesheet: Note the format!

CSS tag, class and ID selectors:
tag: <p> - p{} - apply to all tags
class: <p class="first"> - .first{} - can be used multiple times
ID: <p ID="nav"> - #nav{} - only be used once

div and span:
divs only focus on a portion of the webpage
spans focus on a smaller part in the div portion

Defining colors in CSS: black, red, green
Hex:(red)(green)(blue)

Note the links!

CSS box model: margin, border, padding, content
